  Locus:
    Page: 67
    Verse: 1
Tags:
  - Consciousness
---
The chief delusion of man is his conviction that there are other causes at
work in his life than his own states of consciousness. All that happens to
him, all that is done by him, comes to him as a result of his states of
consciousness.
